This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the limitations of current machine learning techniques and proposes solutions, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for dynamic analysis of malware, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and system and information theory (cs.SI).
